# Responsive Design

# Project Overview

This project demonstrates the implementation of Responsive Web Design using percentage-based widths and CSS media queries.  
The layout automatically adapts to different screen sizes including desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.

The design includes a modern header, hero section, content cards, and footer with a futuristic visual style.

# Objectives Covered

- Use percentage width for flexible layouts
- Implement Flexbox for responsive structure
- Apply media queries for different screen sizes
- Optimize layout for mobile view
- Create a visually modern and creative interface

# Features

- Animated gradient background
- Glassmorphism content cards
- Responsive navigation layout
- Hover effects and transitions
- Flexible card widths using percentages
- Automatic stacking layout on smaller screens

# Responsive Behavior

- Desktop: Cards are displayed side-by-side using percentage widths.
- Tablet: Cards adjust into two columns.
- Mobile: Cards stack vertically for better readability.
- Navigation is simplified on smaller screens.

# Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- Flexbox
- Media Queries
- CSS Animations

# How to Run the Project

1. Save the file as `responsive.html`.
2. Open the file in any web browser.
3. Resize the browser window or use mobile view in developer tools to test responsiveness.

